askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "There is an important advantage in analyzing 3D data, especially ones that originate from comprehensive largescale scans: the entire geometry of an object and its surrounding context are available at once. This can provide strong cues for semantics, layout, occlusion handling, shape completion, amodal detection, etc. This rich geometric information is complementary to the RGB domain, which offers dense appearance features. Hence, there is a great potential in developing models that perform joint or crossmodal learning to enhance the performance. Although several RGB-D [\\[6,](#page-7-0) [7,](#page-7-1) [16,](#page-7-2) [15\\]](#page-7-3) and a few 3D datasets [\\[12,](#page-7-4) [13,](#page-7-5) [14,](#page-7-6) [1\\]](#page-7-7) have been developed to date, the majority of them are limited in the scale, diversity, and/or the number of modalities they provide."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-311,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-312,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-313,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-314,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-315 ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "5"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-311 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "There is an important advantage in analyzing 3D data, especially ones that originate from comprehensive largescale scans: the entire geometry of an object and its surrounding context are available at once."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-312 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "This can provide strong cues for semantics, layout, occlusion handling, shape completion, amodal detection, etc."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-313 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "This rich geometric information is complementary to the RGB domain, which offers dense appearance features."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-314 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "Hence, there is a great potential in developing models that perform joint or crossmodal learning to enhance the performance."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-31-Sentence-315 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 5"@en ;
    domo:Text "Although several RGB-D [\\[6,](#page-7-0) [7,](#page-7-1) [16,](#page-7-2) [15\\]](#page-7-3) and a few 3D datasets [\\[12,](#page-7-4) [13,](#page-7-5) [14,](#page-7-6) [1\\]](#page-7-7) have been developed to date, the majority of them are limited in the scale, diversity, and/or the number of modalities they provide."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "5"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-32 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Over the past few years, advances in the field of 3D imaging have led to manufacturing inexpensive sensors and mainstreaming their use in consumer products (*e.g*. Kinect [\\[5\\]](#page-7-8), Structure Sensor [\\[3\\]](#page-7-9), RealSense [\\[4\\]](#page-7-10), etc). The Computer Vision community has been affected by this change and is experiencing a lot of development in datadriven 2.5D and 3D vision [\\[6,](#page-7-0) [17,](#page-7-11) [18,](#page-7-12) [19,](#page-7-13) [1\\]](#page-7-7). However, the 3D sensing field has recently undergone a follow-up shift with the availability of mature technology for scan-"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-32-Sentence-321,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-32-Sentence-322,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-32-Sentence-323,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-32-Sentence-324 ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "4"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

