    domo:Text "ning *large-scale* spaces, *e.g*."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-38-Sentence-382 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "an entire building."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-38-Sentence-383 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "Such systems can reliably form the 3D point cloud of thousands of square meters with the number of points often exceeding hundreds of millions."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-38-Sentence-384 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "This demands developing methods capable of coping with this scale, and ideally, exploiting the unique characteristics of such data."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 9"@en ;
    domo:Text "To enable parsing the aforementioned goals, we present a 2D-3D semantic dataset that can be used for a plethora of tasks, such as scene understanding, depth estimation, surface normals estimation, object detection, segmentation, amodal detection, and scene reconstruction. Also, the 3D mesh models and equirectangular projections can be used to generate a virtually unlimited number of images, something that is currently possible only in synthetic 3D datasets. The dataset along with 360◦ visualizations is available for download at [http://3Dsemantics.stanford.edu/.](http://3Dsemantics.stanford.edu/)"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39-Sentence-391,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39-Sentence-392,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39-Sentence-393 ;
    askg-onto:index "9"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "3"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39-Sentence-391 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "To enable parsing the aforementioned goals, we present a 2D-3D semantic dataset that can be used for a plethora of tasks, such as scene understanding, depth estimation, surface normals estimation, object detection, segmentation, amodal detection, and scene reconstruction."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39-Sentence-392 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Also, the 3D mesh models and equirectangular projections can be used to generate a virtually unlimited number of images, something that is currently possible only in synthetic 3D datasets."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-3-Paragraph-39-Sentence-393 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "The dataset along with 360◦ visualizations is available for download at [http://3Dsemantics.stanford.edu/.](http://3Dsemantics.stanford.edu/)"@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4 a askg-onto:Section ;
    rdfs:label "Section 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "2. Related Datasets"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasParagraph askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43 ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:level "1"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "14"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "There exist several RGB-D datasets in the literature related to scene understanding; NYU Depth v2[\\[6\\]](#page-7-0), SUN RGBD[\\[7\\]](#page-7-1) and recently SceneNN [\\[16\\]](#page-7-2) are among the prominent ones. The latter provides a larger number of images than the rest, though the increased number originates from densely annotated frames of videos from a smaller number of scenes. Due to the complexity of collecting and densely annotating such data, many synthetic datasets have appeared lately (RGBD: [\\[15\\]](#page-7-3), 3D: [\\[12,](#page-7-4) [13,](#page-7-5) [14\\]](#page-7-6)). Their advantage is that by employing large-scale object libraries (*e.g*. ShapeNet [\\[11\\]](#page-7-14)) one could generate a virtually infinite number of images along with the corresponding semantics."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-411,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-412,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-413,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-414,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-415 ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "5"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-411 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "There exist several RGB-D datasets in the literature related to scene understanding; NYU Depth v2[\\[6\\]](#page-7-0), SUN RGBD[\\[7\\]](#page-7-1) and recently SceneNN [\\[16\\]](#page-7-2) are among the prominent ones."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-412 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "The latter provides a larger number of images than the rest, though the increased number originates from densely annotated frames of videos from a smaller number of scenes."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-413 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "Due to the complexity of collecting and densely annotating such data, many synthetic datasets have appeared lately (RGBD: [\\[15\\]](#page-7-3), 3D: [\\[12,](#page-7-4) [13,](#page-7-5) [14\\]](#page-7-6))."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-414 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "Their advantage is that by employing large-scale object libraries (*e.g*."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-41-Sentence-415 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 5"@en ;
    domo:Text "ShapeNet [\\[11\\]](#page-7-14)) one could generate a virtually infinite number of images along with the corresponding semantics."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "5"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Existing real datasets are relatively limited to one particular task and the 2.5D domain. Recently, [\\[16\\]](#page-7-2) offered watertight mesh models of the reconstructed scenes and [\\[1\\]](#page-7-7) presented a 3D point cloud dataset of large-scale indoor spaces. Although such data can be used for more than semantic detection/segmentation, it is not suitable for tasks across different data dimensionalities and modalities."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42-Sentence-421,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42-Sentence-422,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42-Sentence-423 ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "3"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42-Sentence-421 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "Existing real datasets are relatively limited to one particular task and the 2.5D domain."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42-Sentence-422 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Recently, [\\[16\\]](#page-7-2) offered watertight mesh models of the reconstructed scenes and [\\[1\\]](#page-7-7) presented a 3D point cloud dataset of large-scale indoor spaces."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-42-Sentence-423 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "Although such data can be used for more than semantic detection/segmentation, it is not suitable for tasks across different data dimensionalities and modalities."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "The proposed 2D-3D dataset includes RGB, depth, equirectangular and global XYZ OpenEXR images, as well as 3D meshes and point clouds of the same indoor spaces (Table [1\\)](#page-1-0). The different modalities can be used independently or jointly to develop learning models that seamlessly transcend across domains. Also, using the provided equirectangular images, camera parameters, and 3D mesh models, it is possible to generate additional data tailored to specific tasks. In comparison to existing real-world datasets, it offers a greater number of images as well as additional modalities, such that of equirectangular images or 3D meshes. It also provides consistent annotations across all modalities and dimensions. However, it is currently limited in the number of object and scene categories."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-431,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-432,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-433,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-434,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-435,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-436 ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "6"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-431 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "The proposed 2D-3D dataset includes RGB, depth, equirectangular and global XYZ OpenEXR images, as well as 3D meshes and point clouds of the same indoor spaces (Table [1\\)](#page-1-0)."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-432 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "The different modalities can be used independently or jointly to develop learning models that seamlessly transcend across domains."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-433 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "Also, using the provided equirectangular images, camera parameters, and 3D mesh models, it is possible to generate additional data tailored to specific tasks."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-434 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "In comparison to existing real-world datasets, it offers a greater number of images as well as additional modalities, such that of equirectangular images or 3D meshes."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-435 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 5"@en ;
    domo:Text "It also provides consistent annotations across all modalities and dimensions."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "5"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-4-Paragraph-43-Sentence-436 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 6"@en ;
    domo:Text "However, it is currently limited in the number of object and scene categories."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "6"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5 a askg-onto:Section ;
    rdfs:label "Section 5"@en ;
    domo:Text "3. Dataset Overview"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasParagraph askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51 ;
    askg-onto:index "5"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:level "1"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "8"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "The dataset is collected in 6 large-scale indoor areas that originate from 3 different buildings of mainly educational and office use. For each area, all modalities are registered in the same reference system, yielding pixel to pixel correspondences among them. In a nutshell, the presented dataset contains a total of 70,496 regular RGB and 1,413 equirectangular RGB images, along with their corresponding depths, surface normals, semantic annotations, global XYZ OpenEXR format and camera metadata. In addition, we provide whole building 3D reconstructions as textured meshes, as well as the corresponding 3D semantic meshes. We also include the colored 3D point cloud data of these areas with the total number of 695,878,620 points, that has been previously presented in the Stanford large-scale 3D Indoor Spaces Dataset (S3DIS [\\[1\\]](#page-7-7)). The annotations are instance-level, and consistent across all modalities and correspond to 13 object classes. We refer the readers to Tables [7](#page-7-15) and [3](#page-5-0) for statistics on the scene and object categories. Figure [3](#page-3-0) shows an example of the equirectangular images for one scan."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasCitation "[3]",
        "[7]" ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-511,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-512,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-513,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-514,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-515,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-516,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-517,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-5-Paragraph-51-Sentence-518 ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "8"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

