askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-710 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 10"@en ;
    domo:Text "We then project the object and scene semantics on the"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-710-Sentence-7101 ;
    askg-onto:index "10"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "1"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-710-Sentence-7101 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "We then project the object and scene semantics on the"@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 11"@en ;
    domo:Text "mesh model's faces and generate 3D semantic meshes that preserves the same class structure and instance index. We used a voting scheme to transfer these annotations to the mesh. Each annotated point casts a vote for the face that is nearest to it, then votes are tallied and each face is annotated with the mode class. Faces which garner no votes belong to non-annotated parts of the dataset and are labeled as the default *0* *0 0* class (null). Our 3D models are labeled with the class of the object and the specific instance. These instances are globally unique among all models and are indexed in semantic labels.json. Each object is stored in this file as class instanceNum roomT ype roomNum areaNum. Note that instances, rooms and areas are 1-indexed so that the singleton class is unique in that it has instanceNum = 0, roomNum = 0 and areaNum = 0. Figure [2](#page-2-0) shows the raw and semantically annotated 3D mesh models for all 6 areas."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasCitation "[2]" ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7111,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7112,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7113,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7114,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7115,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7116,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7117,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7118,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7119 ;
    askg-onto:index "11"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "9"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7111 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "mesh model's faces and generate 3D semantic meshes that preserves the same class structure and instance index."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7112 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "We used a voting scheme to transfer these annotations to the mesh."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7113 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "Each annotated point casts a vote for the face that is nearest to it, then votes are tallied and each face is annotated with the mode class."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7114 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "Faces which garner no votes belong to non-annotated parts of the dataset and are labeled as the default *0* *0 0* class (null)."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7115 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 5"@en ;
    domo:Text "Our 3D models are labeled with the class of the object and the specific instance."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "5"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7116 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 6"@en ;
    domo:Text "These instances are globally unique among all models and are indexed in semantic labels.json."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "6"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7117 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 7"@en ;
    domo:Text "Each object is stored in this file as class instanceNum roomT ype roomNum areaNum."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "7"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7118 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 8"@en ;
    domo:Text "Note that instances, rooms and areas are 1-indexed so that the singleton class is unique in that it has instanceNum = 0, roomNum = 0 and areaNum = 0."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "8"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-711-Sentence-7119 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 9"@en ;
    domo:Text "Figure [2](#page-2-0) shows the raw and semantically annotated 3D mesh models for all 6 areas."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasCitation "[2]" ;
    askg-onto:index "9"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-72 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "3D Point Cloud and Mesh: As mentioned above, we"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-72-Sentence-721 ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "1"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-72-Sentence-721 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "3D Point Cloud and Mesh: As mentioned above, we"@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "receive the reconstructed 3D textured Mesh model for each scanned area from the Matterport Camera. Each model contains an average of 200k triangulated faces and a material mapping to texture images providing a realistic reconstruction of the scanned space. We generate the colored 3D point clouds by densely and uniformly sampling points on the mesh surface and assigning the corresponding color."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73-Sentence-731,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73-Sentence-732,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73-Sentence-733 ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "3"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73-Sentence-731 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "receive the reconstructed 3D textured Mesh model for each scanned area from the Matterport Camera."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73-Sentence-732 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Each model contains an average of 200k triangulated faces and a material mapping to texture images providing a realistic reconstruction of the scanned space."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-73-Sentence-733 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "We generate the colored 3D point clouds by densely and uniformly sampling points on the mesh surface and assigning the corresponding color."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-74 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "3D Semantics (Labeled Mesh and Voxels): We semantically annotate the data on the *3D point cloud* and assign one of the following 13 object classes on a per-point basis: *ceiling, floor, wall, beam, column, window, door, table, chair, sofa, bookcase, board* and *clutter* for all other elements. Performing annotations in 3D, rather than 2D, provides 3D object models and enables performing occlusion and amodal analysis, yet the semantics can be projected"@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-74-Sentence-741,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-74-Sentence-742 ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "2"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-74-Sentence-741 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "3D Semantics (Labeled Mesh and Voxels): We semantically annotate the data on the *3D point cloud* and assign one of the following 13 object classes on a per-point basis: *ceiling, floor, wall, beam, column, window, door, table, chair, sofa, bookcase, board* and *clutter* for all other elements."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-74-Sentence-742 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Performing annotations in 3D, rather than 2D, provides 3D object models and enables performing occlusion and amodal analysis, yet the semantics can be projected"@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

