askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-79 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 9"@en ;
    domo:Text "onto any number of images to provide ground truth annotations in 2D as well. Each object instance in the dataset has a unique identifier. We also annotate the point cloud data into rooms and assign one of the following 11 scene labels to each: *office, conference room, hallway, auditorium, open space, lobby, lounge, pantry, copy room, storage* and *WC*. Again, each instance in the point cloud receives a unique index. Given these annotations, we calculate the tightest axis-aligned object bounding box of each instance and further voxelize it into a 6 × 6 × 6 grid with binary occupancy. This information provides a better understanding of the underlying geometry and can be leveraged, for example, in 3D object detection or classification."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-79-Sentence-791,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-7-Paragraph-79-Sentence-792,
