askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 21"@en ;
    domo:Text "computed from a normals pass in Blender and are saved as 24-bit RBG PNGs. The surface normals in 3D corresponding to each pixel are computed from the 3D mesh instead of directly from the depth image. The normal vector is saved in the RGB color value where Red is the horizontal value (more red to the right), Green is vertical (more green downwards), and Blue is towards the camera. Each channel is 127.5-centered, so both values to the left and right (of the axis) are possible. For example, a surface normal pointing straight at the camera would be colored (128, 128, 255) since pixels must be integer-valued."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8211,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8212,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8213,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8214,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8215 ;
    askg-onto:index "21"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "5"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8211 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "computed from a normals pass in Blender and are saved as 24-bit RBG PNGs."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8212 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "The surface normals in 3D corresponding to each pixel are computed from the 3D mesh instead of directly from the depth image."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8213 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "The normal vector is saved in the RGB color value where Red is the horizontal value (more red to the right), Green is vertical (more green downwards), and Blue is towards the camera."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8214 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "Each channel is 127.5-centered, so both values to the left and right (of the axis) are possible."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-821-Sentence-8215 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 5"@en ;
    domo:Text "For example, a surface normal pointing straight at the camera would be colored (128, 128, 255) since pixels must be integer-valued."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "5"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-822 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 22"@en ;
    domo:Text "Missing values take (128,128,128) which is convenient in practice as it is not a unit normal and is clearly visually distinguishable from the surrounding values. The convention is that surface normals cannot point away from the camera."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-822-Sentence-8221,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-822-Sentence-8222 ;
    askg-onto:index "22"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "2"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-822-Sentence-8221 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "Missing values take (128,128,128) which is convenient in practice as it is not a unit normal and is clearly visually distinguishable from the surrounding values."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-822-Sentence-8222 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "The convention is that surface normals cannot point away from the camera."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 23"@en ;
    domo:Text "Semantically Labeled Images: We project the 3D semantics from the mesh model onto the 2D image. Due to certain geometric artifacts present at the mesh model mainly because of the level of detail in the reconstruction, the 2D annotations occasionally present small local misalignment to the underlying pixels, especially for points that have a short distance to the camera. This issue can be easily addressed by fusing image content with the projected annotations using graphical models."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823-Sentence-8231,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823-Sentence-8232,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823-Sentence-8233 ;
    askg-onto:index "23"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "3"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823-Sentence-8231 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "Semantically Labeled Images: We project the 3D semantics from the mesh model onto the 2D image."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823-Sentence-8232 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "Due to certain geometric artifacts present at the mesh model mainly because of the level of detail in the reconstruction, the 2D annotations occasionally present small local misalignment to the underlying pixels, especially for points that have a short distance to the camera."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-823-Sentence-8233 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "This issue can be easily addressed by fusing image content with the projected annotations using graphical models."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 24"@en ;
    domo:Text "The semantically labeled images are saved as 24 bit RGB PNGs, but each pixel's color value can be directly interpreted as an index into the list. For example, board 3 hallway 4 6 is at index 257 in semantics labels.json. Since 257 equals #000101 in hex, #000101 is the color of the chair in the image. For semantic images, pixel values that correspond to holes in the mesh contain the value (13, 13, 13)."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8241,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8242,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8243,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8244 ;
    askg-onto:index "24"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "4"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8241 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "The semantically labeled images are saved as 24 bit RGB PNGs, but each pixel's color value can be directly interpreted as an index into the list."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8242 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "For example, board 3 hallway 4 6 is at index 257 in semantics labels.json."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8243 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "Since 257 equals #000101 in hex, #000101 is the color of the chair in the image."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-824-Sentence-8244 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "For semantic images, pixel values that correspond to holes in the mesh contain the value (13, 13, 13)."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825 a askg-onto:Paragraph ;
    rdfs:label "Paragraph 25"@en ;
    domo:Text "3D Coordinate Encoded Images: The pixels in these images encode the X, Y, Z location of the point in the world coordinate system. This information can be used for conveniently relating the content of the RGB images, *e.g*. forming correspondences. The images are stored in the OpenEXR format with each channel contiaining 16-bit floating point numbers. Utility functions, including for reading EXRs, are provided in the GitHub repo accessible on the website."@en ;
    askg-onto:hasSentence askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8251,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8252,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8253,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8254,
        askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8255 ;
    askg-onto:index "25"^^xsd:int ;
    askg-onto:numberOfSentences "5"^^xsd:positiveInteger .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8251 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 1"@en ;
    domo:Text "3D Coordinate Encoded Images: The pixels in these images encode the X, Y, Z location of the point in the world coordinate system."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "1"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8252 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 2"@en ;
    domo:Text "This information can be used for conveniently relating the content of the RGB images, *e.g*."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "2"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8253 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 3"@en ;
    domo:Text "forming correspondences."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "3"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8254 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 4"@en ;
    domo:Text "The images are stored in the OpenEXR format with each channel contiaining 16-bit floating point numbers."@en ;
    askg-onto:index "4"^^xsd:int .

askg-data:Paper-170201105v2-Section-8-Paragraph-825-Sentence-8255 a askg-onto:Sentence ;
    rdfs:label "Sentence 5"@en ;
